New favorite taco spot!
I discovered this gem after church service on Sunday, and I‚Äôm so glad I did! I ordered the chilaquiles with green salsa, and WOW absolutely delicious. The flavors were fresh, vibrant, and perfectly balanced. You can tell everything is made with care. The staff was friendly, the atmosphere was casual and welcoming, and I can‚Äôt wait to go back to try more of the menu. Highly recommend if you‚Äôre in the area and craving authentic, flavorful Mexican food!

Nice spot in Thousand Oaks. Cozy atmosphere. Eating outside in covered area is decent. Tacos reasonably priced and taste was adequate. Nothing to write home about. Will try nachos and burritos if in the area again.

Love their street tacos, chorizo and papas is my fave. My kids love the carne asada and it‚Äôs family friendly so we enjoy sitting at the long tables on the porch. More faves are their homemade aquas frescas, try jamaica or
watermelon. New to menu is quesa birria. Quesadilla with very flavorful slow cooked beef and broth for dipping or sipping. Yum.
The service was amazing, and it‚Äôs a cute taco place I only came for breakfast and the green chilaquiles were crispy and tasty.

There were heaters outside so eating there was comfortable. Service was great. Polite n friendly staff with smiles from when I walked in till I left.  I had the quesabirria tacos n can honestly say they were the BEST I'VE EVER HAD. Tortilla held up to the last bite. They know what they're doing. I'm definitely coming back n highly recommend you try it if you haven't already.

detailedReviews.text: The birria burrito tastes like something from a low-income public school cafeteria or it was frozen and just heated it up for my order. detailedReviews.author: Jaimene Washington
detailedReviews.text: The food is good not great, I liked the potato taco, but overall it‚Äôs not the best option anymore. Tacos are expensive for what you get (about $3 for a small potato taco), and they charge extra for salsa if you want more than the one they give you for the entire meal. They also charge a fee if you pay with a credit card, so it‚Äôs better to bring cash. The staff often seem more focused on talking to each other than greeting customers, and there are a lot of strict rules ‚Äî including no dogs allowed even on the outdoor patio and the door that is facing the parking lot is exit only- and yes they care. They want you to walk to the sidewalk and go in.  It just feels awkward / not super welcoming.

Overall this was  slightly better than say Baja Fresh or other chain ‚Äútaco/ burrito ‚Äù food. We also tried the birria tacos, a bit more flavor yea but still not on a wow level.

detailedReviews.author: J Dorman
detailedReviews.text: Most of the time the food is definitely good. Unfortunately every time I come the vibe of the workers is not friendly at all. Today the guy who was bringing out the food had an excellent attitude and vibe. When he brought my daughter her food she took a couple bites and as she realized it was the wrong burrito and at the same time, he came out and said it was the wrong burrito.  He offered the correct burrito and she asked if she could just have the burrito on the next visit. He told her when she was done  to come inside and give her info. A while later another server came out and brought the burrito. We explained everything that previously happened and she went in to talk to the owner. The owner was not customer friendly and neither honored what the original server agreed to and did not give the already made burrito.  Besides today's incident I will say they are never very friendly when taking orders which is a shame because the food is decent but they just kill the experience. I keep saying I won't go back and end up there. After today we won't be going back. The owner is not nice or customer friendly.

This should be a wonderful spot.  I'm not from around here.  In the area for work.  Saw this place, thought I'd try the tacos.
Such a nice looking spot!.   It has what I was looking for to relax, do some computer work and enjoy a meal.  Well, here is the prob;
-  Real tacos not sold here.  Only the tiny street tacos
-  price way too high for street tacos.  Should be $1.50 each but they are nearly $4 plus each
-  no wifi
-  no power outlets for computer
-  no paper towels in bathroom
-  no beer to enjoy while waiting
-  food has no flavor.  .I mean just add some salt!  Nothing!!
-  salsa is very watery and no flavor

So, 7 tiny tacos...no drink...$23.
As I sit here, I see a lunch spit across the street.  I think I should have gone there.
